### Conditional Statements in C#

Conditional statements control the flow of execution based on boolean conditions.

### The if Statement

The `if` statement executes a block of code if a condition is true:

```csharp
if (condition)
{
    // Code to execute if condition is true
}
```

### Comparison and Logical Operators

| Operator | Meaning | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `==` | Equal to | `if (x == 5)` |
| `!=` | Not equal to | `if (x != 5)` |
| `>` | Greater than | `if (x > 5)` |
| `<` | Less than | `if (x < 5)` |
| `>=` | Greater or equal | `if (x >= 5)` |
| `<=` | Less or equal | `if (x <= 5)` |
| `&&` | AND | `if (x > 0 && x < 100)` |
| `||` | OR | `if (x < 0 || x > 100)` |
| `!` | NOT | `if (!isComplete)` |

### Boolean Expressions

Any expression that evaluates to `true` or `false`:

```csharp
int age = 18;
bool canVote = age >= 18;  // true

if (canVote)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Eligible to vote");
}

if (age >= 18 && age <= 65)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Working age");
}
```

### Nested Conditions

```csharp
if (isLoggedIn)
{
    if (isAdmin)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Admin panel");
    }
    else
    {
        Console.WriteLine("User dashboard");
    }
}
```

### Common Patterns

```csharp
// Range check
if (temperature >= 0 && temperature <= 100)
{
    Console.WriteLine("Water is liquid");
}

// Null check
if (name != null)
{
    Console.WriteLine(name.Length);
}
```

> **Key Point:** Conditions must evaluate to a boolean value. C# does not treat non-boolean values like 0 or 1 as true/false. Use `&&` for AND and `||` for OR with short-circuit evaluation.

### Pattern Matching in Conditions (C# 7+)

```csharp
if (obj is string str)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"String length: {str.Length}");
}
```

codeExample:
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        int age = 25;
        bool hasLicense = true;

        if (age >= 18 && hasLicense)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("You can drive");
        }
        else if (age >= 18 && !hasLicense)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Get a license first");
        }
        else
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Too young to drive");
        }
    }
}
